main event: On 2 August 1966, a civilian reported observing a white object in Oaklawn, Illinois, which changed movement and was presumed related to a missile launch.
interesting points: The observation lasted for approximately 10 seconds., The object was moving north at the time of the sighting., Multiple witnesses reported seeing unusual activity in the area., Witnesses described the object as disc-shaped with a soft blue-white light., The report concluded that there was insufficient data for evaluation.
